# QSIPrep Project Rules

## Project Identity

- Package: `qsiprep` -- diffusion MRI preprocessing BIDS App
- Default branch: `master` (migration to `main` is planned)
- Entry point: [qsiprep/cli/run.py](mdc:qsiprep/cli/run.py)

## Linting & Formatting

- Config: [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml) under `[tool.ruff]`
- Pre-commit: [.pre-commit-config.yaml](mdc:.pre-commit-config.yaml) with ruff v0.6.2
- Black is disabled (`[tool.black] exclude = ".*"`)

### Suppressed Lint Rules (TODO)

The following rules are suppressed in pyproject.toml with `# TODO: Fix these`:
S605, DTZ005, B904, A001, B006, S607, S108, S602, E402, UP028, UP031, BLE001

When touching code that triggers these rules, fix the violation.

## Key Module Paths

- DWI workflows: `qsiprep/workflows/dwi/` (hmc, hmc_sdc, fsl, resampling, confounds, etc.)
- Anatomical workflows: `qsiprep/workflows/anatomical/`
- Fieldmap workflows: `qsiprep/workflows/fieldmap/` (pepolar, phdiff, syn, drbuddi)
- External tool interfaces: `qsiprep/interfaces/` (eddy, mrtrix, dsi_studio, dipy, tortoise, freesurfer)
- Config: [qsiprep/config.py](mdc:qsiprep/config.py)

## Testing

- Test extras: `tests` in pyproject.toml
- Parallel test execution supported via `pytest-xdist`
- Integration test markers defined in `[tool.pytest.ini_options]`
- Environment variable `RUNNING_PYTEST=1` is set during test runs
